 %7C&amp\;sdata=CgVi3h41%2BPSxH9LGy3iGrIcKoQfIDlzaZJGdgRzCoJg%3D&amp\;rese
 rved=0)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Returning JD students are invited to jo
 in the Office for Student Affairs and the Academic Success and Bar Suppor
 t program for a Zoom workshop regarding fall course registration on Wedne
 sday\, March 25 at 5:00 pm.</p><p>  We will walk through graduation requi
 rements\, academic regulations\, and curricular considerations to take in
 to account when planning a course schedule. We will also talk about what 
 courses will best prepare students for the doctrinal and skills portions 
 of the bar exam. Lastly\, we will discuss the new tool students will use 
 to register for courses\, Stellic\, and identify resources so that will p
 repare students to use it.</p><p>  We strongly encourage all 1Ls to atten
 d this Zoom session since it is their first time selecting courses. We st
 rongly encourage all 2Ls to attend since it is their first time using Ste
