SUMMARY:AlgoRhythms 2026: The Law's Role in Forming Creative Norms
DESCRIPTION:The Indiana University Maurer School of Law is pleased to par
 ticipate once again in AlgoRhythms 2026\, the third annual conference pre
 sented in collaboration with the Indiana University Jacobs School of Musi
 c exploring the intersection of music and artificial intelligence.  As a 
 part of the larger program\, Maurer will host a panel discussion titled L
 egal Challenges and Opportunities in Music &amp\; AI featuring Dan Amin '
 06.Panelists:Dan Amin '06 (Assistant Chief Counsel\, Lucasfilm)  John Str
 ohm (Partner\, Meitus Strohm\, LLP)  Sean O'Connor (Downtown Music)  Rain
 a Murnak (University of Miami)  Moderated by 3L Kayla Behforouz    All bi
 os can be viewed here: https://blogs.iu.edu/jsominnovation/2026-summit-pa
 rticipants/ (https://blogs.iu.edu/jsominnovation/2026-summit-participants
 /)AlgoRhythms 2026\, March 26-2028. See a Full schedule of all AlgoRhythm
 s events here: https://blogs.iu.edu/jsominnovation/algorhythms-the-world-
 of-music-and-ai/ (https://blogs.iu.edu/jsominnovation/algorhythms-the-wor
 ld-of-music-and-ai/)  Sign up to attend: https://forms.office.com/r/4QgGS
 dDfzp (https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2F
