X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The Indiana University Maurer School of
  Law is pleased to participate once again in AlgoRhythms 2026\, the third
  annual conference presented in collaboration with the Indiana University
  Jacobs School of Music exploring the intersection of music and artificia
 l intelligence.</p><p>  As a part of the larger program\, Maurer will hos
 t a panel discussion titled <strong><em>Legal Challenges and Opportunitie
 s in Music &amp\; AI</em></strong> featuring Dan Amin '06.</p><p><strong>
 Panelists:</strong></p><ul><li>Dan Amin '06 (Assistant Chief Counsel\, Lu
 casfilm)  </li><li>John Strohm (Partner\, Meitus Strohm\, LLP)  </li><li>
 Sean O'Connor (Downtown Music)  </li><li>Raina Murnak (University of Miam
 i)  </li><li>Moderated by 3L Kayla Behforouz  </li></ul><p>  All bios can
  be viewed here: <a href="https://blogs.iu.edu/jsominnovation/2026-summit
 -participants/">https://blogs.iu.edu/jsominnovation/2026-summit-participa
 nts/</a></p><p><strong>AlgoRhythms 2026</strong>\, March 26-2028. See a F
 ull schedule of all AlgoRhythms events here: <a href="https://blogs.iu.ed
 u/jsominnovation/algorhythms-the-world-of-music-and-ai/">https://blogs.iu
 .edu/jsominnovation/algorhythms-the-world-of-music-and-ai/</a></p><p>  Si
