SUMMARY:Apples to Oranges? Comparing Constitutions
DESCRIPTION:Marton Sulyok\, visiting researcher at the Georgetown Law Cen
 ter for the Constitution\, joined by Professor Timothy Waters\, will comp
 are constitutions across the globe in their treatment of the rights guara
 nteed by the First Amendment to the United States Constitution. What can 
 the United States learn from other constitutions? How can our First Amend
 ment influence other nations' respect for the rights of their citizens? J
 oin us for a discussion of our Constitution as the 250th anniversary of o
 ur Nation approaches\, and what can be learned by examining different app
 roaches to expressive rights.  Dave's Hot Chicken will be provided for al
 l attendees!&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Marton Sulyok\, visiting researcher at 
 the Georgetown Law Center for the Constitution\, joined by Professor Timo
 thy Waters\, will compare constitutions across the globe in their treatme
 nt of the rights guaranteed by the First Amendment to the United States C
 onstitution. What can the United States learn from other constitutions? H
 ow can our First Amendment influence other nations' respect for the right
 s of their citizens? Join us for a discussion of our Constitution as the 
 250th anniversary of our Nation approaches\, and what can be learned by e
 xamining different approaches to expressive rights.</p><p>  Dave's Hot Ch
 icken will be provided for all attendees!&#160\;</p>
